Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.42,0:00:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,REORDER. Class IX demand forecasting for contested logistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.42,0:00:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,LOGCOM use case: predict Class IX consumption for a deployed MAGTF.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.42,0:00:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,OPTEMPO, environment, and historical maintenance drive the forecast.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.42,0:00:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety days of GCSS-MC work orders stream in. No data movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.43,0:00:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A Holt-Winters forecaster projects each NSN thirty, sixty, ninety days\Nout.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A Kamiwaza-deployed model judges each top-N NSN — RED, AMBER, GREEN —\Nwith a pre-position action.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.07,0:00:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sortable risk table. Pre-position by depot and date. One sustainment\Nbrief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.07,0:00:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward nodes plus recommended pre-position flows on the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.08,0:00:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL and the same code runs inside the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.08,0:01:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Powered by the Kamiwaza Stack. Deploy in hours, not months.
